<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,654,1435]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,654,679]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum black with mosaic of small yellow maculae. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[1170,1261,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
) with pair of anteromedian diagonal black arches medially connected. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[973,1063,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
) with posterior portion bluish. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[302,385,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
) yellow with black maculae on mesoscutum. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1117,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
) red; clavus with numerous bluish-white maculae and narrow stripes; claval sulcus with black stripe bordered by narrow bluish-white stripes; costal area with two longitudinal adjacent stripes, innermost irregular and bluish-white, outermost black; outer discal cell with irregular bluish-white stripe; outer apical portion with bluish-white maculae; apex gray. Face black with mosaic of small yellow maculae. Clypeus with ventral black macula. Male pygofer with posterior margin truncate (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[257,517,906,931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="c">Young 1977, fig. 749c</bibRefCitation>
) and long paired process on inner ventroapical portion (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[1161,1425,906,931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="p">Young 1977, fig. 749p</bibRefCitation>
). Paraphyses with basal sclerite symmetrical and rami minute (vestigial) (
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[980,1245,942,967]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="q">Young 1977, fig. 749q</bibRefCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with hook-shaped basiventral paired processes, symmetrical and anteriorly directed. Female sternite VII similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[233,358,1015,1039]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis box="[233,358,1015,1039]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">A. fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[533,615,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) with two broad superposed sclerotized plates, dorsalmost elliptical and ventralmost bilobate, with broad and deep subtriangular anteromedian emargination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,654,1435]" box="[199,611,1086,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
Female length. 
<quantity box="[372,521,1087,1111]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" metricValueMax="10.1" metricValueMin="9.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="9.6" valueMax="10.1" valueMin="9.1">9.1–10.1 mm</quantity>
(n = 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,654,1435]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,576,1122,1147]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[928,1053,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis box="[928,1053,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">A. fraterna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1315,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with two broad, superposed sclerotized plates, dorsalmost plate elliptical, ventralmost plate bilobate with broad and deep subtriangular median emargination on anterior margin and slight median concavity on posterior margin. Pygofer similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[533,653,1231,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[533,653,1231,1254]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula I, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[967,1051,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), with basal portion slightly broad with small lateral prominence; basal margin obliquely truncate; blade similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[1179,1303,1267,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1179,1303,1267,1290]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[349,471,1303,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[349,471,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; teeth, on median portion (
<figureCitation box="[782,867,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 51 – 61" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1676,1699]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,194,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[164,1422,193,1655]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 51 – 61. (51 – 56) Apogonalia interrupta (Signoret, 1855), female: 51, dorsal habitus; 52, left forewing, lateral view; 53, sternite VII, ventral view; 54, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 55, pygofer, lateral view; 56, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (57 – 60) A. krameri Young, 1977, female: 57, dorsal habitus; 58, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 59, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 60, valvula II, tooth on median portion, lateral view. (61) A. loxa Freytag, 2004, female: 61, dorsal habitus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035596/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
), very prominent, 1.5 to 2 times longer than high, spaced from one another about one tooth length; preapical prominence anterior to anteapical tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
